The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
		 Wednesday, June 30, 2004  Suchetana BhattacharjeeSuchetana BhattacharjeeSocial activistCrimes against women are as serious a problem in West Bengal as in the rest of the country. But recent developments reflecting the attitude of some people against criminals are haunting me. Those who want to let criminals like Dhananjoy Chatterjee go are morally absolving them of the crimes they commit against women and humanity. Mercy sends the message that even after committing such a brutal act they can be welcomed back into the mainstream. Are those raising these confusing philosophical debates aware that the majority stands against leniency?
